text:
Alexander Nikolas Walzer
Switzerland
awalzer@ethz.ch
Summary
interested in open innovation and entrepreneurship for AEC technologies
Experience
Independent Consultant
walzer.tech
Apr 2019 - Present (1 year 10 months +)
Full-stack AEC technology consulting services that include market research, product/system R&D
paired with strategy and business development reports. Clients are design agencies, ConTech and
SaaS Startups, Non-profit organizations and VC funds in EU and the US, as well as construction
industry conglomerates.
IMCRC Research Fellow
RMIT University
Jan 2020 - Jan 2021 (1 year 1 month)
We streamline the process between design and custom manufacturing. Based inside the Architectural
Robotics Lab at RMIT School of Architecture and Design we are developing bespoke robotized
processes for Australian SMEs, such as Wire-arc Additive Manufacturing (WAAM) Metal 3D
Printing and Incremental Sheetforming (ISF) - we do this in close collaboration with UAP Company,
UoWollongong, FIF and the QUT in Brisbane. This collaborative research is made possible by the
Innovative Manufacturing Cooperative Research Centre (IMCRC) in Design Robotics. Pro-active
industry knowledge transfer is conducted through the Open Innovation Network, affiliated seminars,
webinars and demos at the ARMHub.
NCCR Research Assistant
ETH Zürich
Jan 2016 - Dec 2019 (4 years)
Gramazio Kohler Research / NCCR Digital Fabrication: working on Mesh Mould with the In-Situ
Fabricator, incl. the NCCR dfabhouse 1:1 demonstrator at the Empa NEST building, tutoring in the
Architecture BSc., MSc. and MAS Postgrad Digital Fabrication Programme, close collaborator with the
ADRL, Disney Research Zurich’s Computational Design and Manufacturing Group and Swiss Industry
partners Zühlke, Schlatter, Bürgin 3D Creations. ETH StudentProjectHouse: Makerspace manager and
collaborator. D-ARCH Rapid Architectural Prototyping Lab (RapLab): RA (Digital Prototyping)
FabLab Intern / Trainee
Fab Lab Barcelona
Feb 2015 - Jun 2015 (5 months)
R&D in both IaaC and Valldaura Labs. Projects include the Smart Citizen Kit, a WikiHouse (built with AA
students in a week) and an Open Source Deltabot (as part of MIT FabAcademy).
Alexander Nikolas Walzer - page 1

Education
ETH Zürich
Doctor of Science, Entrepreneurship for Digital Fabrication and Robotics in AEC
2021 - 2024
The Chair of Innovative and Industrial Construction (Prof. Dr. Hall) seeks to increase innovation in
the built environment by investigating how new forms of process, organization, and information can
integrate the supply chain of the vertically, horizontally, and longitudinally fragmented construction
industry. Our research and teaching focus includes lean management processes to improve
productivity, digital building information modeling to improve coordination, new forms of project
delivery to govern complex projects, and new organizational orientations to spark entrepreneurship for
industrialized construction in the developed and developing world.
Technische Universität Wien
Master of Science (MSc) / Dipl.-Ing., Architecture, Spatial Planning
2016 - 2018
Diploma thesis: E Mare Libertas (Prof. Dr. Berthold) - Archdiploma19; eVolo & 3DHubs shortlist. This
project looked at densification strategies for Singapore and proposed a vertically stacked, modular
skyscraper on the sea using generative design and environmental analysis.
Leopold-Franzens Universität Innsbruck
Bachelor of Science (BSc), Architecture
2013 - 2014
Bachelorthesis Prof. Theo Spyropolous (Director AADRL), Electives at ioud and Studio FRoche
RMIT University
Architecture
2015 - 2015
Robotic Fabrication Studio with M. d. Campo (Award of Excellence Shortlist), Slowbotics Elective (G.
Jahn), RMIT Mace (3D printed Titanium at AMP), Texas FieldConstruct Pavilion (R. Snooks).
Politecnico di Milano
Architectural Sciences
2012 - 2013
Language stay Como (one month) and Perugia (one month). Travelling Workshops, Parametric Design
and Geometry Coursework.
Licenses & Certifications
Fab(rication) Academy - Massachusetts Institute of Technology
Australian Manufacturing Academy - Advanced Manufacturing Growth Centre Ltd
Technology Entrepreneurship: Lab to Market - HarvardX
Alexander Nikolas Walzer - page 2

Skills
Architectural Design   •   Rapid Prototyping   •   3D Printing   •   Information Architecture   •   Design Research   •  
Robotics   •   Consulting   •   Business Strategy   •   Project Management   •   Design Thinking
Honors & Awards
Erasmus Exchange Scholarship - Austrian Exchange Service (OeAD)
Sep 2012
Scholarship for studying at Politecnico di Milano (Italy).
ABB Robotics Mobility Grant - ABB Robotics
May 2014
Mobility Grant awarded by ABB Robotics for young researches in the field of robotics in Architecture at
the Rob|Arch2014 conference, University of Michigan (US).
Leonardo da Vinci Grant - European Comission Life Long Learning Programme
(LLP)
Feb 2015
Scholarship for working at Fabrication Laboratory (FabLab) / IaaC Barcelona (Spain).
Joint Study Scholarship - State of Tyrol, Austria
Jul 2015
Scholarship for studying at RMIT University (Australia).
Swiss Technology Award - Swiss Innovation Forum
Nov 2016
The project team behind the novel building technology «Mesh Mould» received the Swiss Technology
Award 2016 in the category «Inventors». The award is Switzerland's most prestigious award for
innovation and technology. «Mesh Mould» allows to build load-bearing concrete elements of any shape
without formwork.
Concrete Innovation Conference (CIC) Award 2017 - Norwegian Concrete
Association
Mar 2017
The Mesh Mould project team received the award in the category “Buildability – Efficient Construction
Techniques” for their presentation “Mesh Mould – an On-site, Robotically Fabricated Functional
Formwork”.
Archdiploma 2019 Exhibition - TU Wien
Nov 2019
Diploma thesis biennal exhibition at TVFA Hall in Vienna (1/56 chosen projects of two years)
Project: "E Mare Libertas" on modular construction for stacked off-shore housing in Singapore
Alexander Nikolas Walzer - page 3
